currentDoc: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

currentSuggestions.original: You remove the bee from your shoulder and it flies back to its hive.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: You remove the bee from your shoulder and it flies back to its hive.

currentSuggestions.original: You have to figure out a way to escape your palace without anyone noticing.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: You have to figure out a way to escape your palace without anyone noticing.

currentSuggestions.original: You look down and see a bee wearing a tiny cap and vest.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: You look down and see a bee wearing a tiny cap and vest.
